{"allOf":[{"type":"object","properties":{"@context":{"oneOf":[{"type":"string"},{"type":"object","properties":{"@vocab":{"type":"string"},"hydra":{"type":"string","enum":["http://www.w3.org/ns/hydra/core#"]}},"required":["@vocab","hydra"],"additionalProperties":true}]},"@id":{"type":"string"},"@type":{"type":"string"}},"required":["@id","@type"],"x-readme-ref-name":"HydraItemBaseSchema"},{"type":"object","properties":{"project":{"type":"string","format":"iri-reference","example":"https://example.com/"},"name":{"type":"string"},"cronExpression":{"description":"Standard 5-field cron expression: `m h dom mon dow`","default":"0 9 * * 1","type":"string"},"timezone":{"default":"Europe/Berlin","type":"string"},"nextRunAt":{"type":["string","null"],"format":"date-time"},"lastRunAt":{"type":["string","null"],"format":"date-time"},"isEnabled":{"default":true,"type":"boolean"},"taskTitle":{"type":"string"},"taskDescription":{"type":["string","null"]},"taskPriority":{"default":"normal","type":"string"},"taskEstimatedMinutes":{"type":["integer","null"]},"taskAssignee":{"type":["string","null"],"format":"iri-reference","example":"https://example.com/"},"id":{"readOnly":true,"type":["string","null"],"format":"uuid"},"createdAt":{"readOnly":true,"type":"string","format":"date-time"},"updatedAt":{"readOnly":true,"type":"string","format":"date-time"},"workspace":{"type":"string","format":"iri-reference","example":"https://example.com/"},"version":{"readOnly":true,"default":1,"type":"integer"},"createdByUser":{"type":["string","null"],"format":"iri-reference","example":"https://example.com/"},"updatedByUser":{"type":["string","null"],"format":"iri-reference","example":"https://example.com/"},"enabled":{"readOnly":true,"type":"boolean"}}}],"description":"\"Every X, create a Task in project Y\" — recurring task definition.\n\nMVP: stores a cron expression (`0 9 * * 1` = Mondays 9am) plus a Task\ntemplate inline (title/description/priority/estimatedMinutes). When\n`app:tasks:run-schedules` fires and `nextRunAt <= now`, the schedule\nspawns a Task in `project` with these defaults and re-computes\n`nextRunAt`.\n\nStoring a TaskTemplate FK would be cleaner (reusable templates) but\n\"every X create THIS specific task\" is the 90% use case — inline keeps\nthe data model flat and the cron worker self-contained.","x-readme-ref-name":"TaskSchedule.jsonld"}